<body>
<div class="logo">
<center><img src="allthethings.jpeg" width="800px"></center>
</div>

<div id="header">

<p>
<h2>The most important part of a software bug's life is triage.</h2>
</p>
</div>

<div id="content">

<p>
Sorting, filtering and analyzing bugs every day helps Mozilla find problems 
sooner and ship great software to hundreds of millions of users. 
</p>

<p>
If you can spare a few minutes a day, you can help Mozilla move faster. 
Sign up below; enter your name, Bugzilla email address, and a maximum number
of bugs we can send you.  
</p>

<p>
Once a week, five days a week or every day if you like, we'll send you an email 
with links to new issues our community is facing so you can help get them 
to the right place and the right person with the right information.
</p>

<p>
<form action="index.py" method="post">
Name or IRC handle: <input type="text" name="nickname"/><br/>
Email: <input type="text" name="email" /><br/>
Number of bugs:
<select name="number">
<option value="1">1</option>
<option value="2">2</option>
<option value="3">3</option>
<option value="5">5</option>
<option value="8">8</option>
<option value="12">12</option>
<option value="15">15</option>
</select><br/>
How often? 
<select name="rate">
<option value="daily">Daily</option>
<option value="workdays">Mon-Fri</option>
<option value="weekly">Weekly</option>
</select>
</p>
<p>
 <input type="submit" value="Submit"></p>
</form>
</p>
</div>

<p>
If you're just getting started with Mozilla's bug tracker, you'll also need to <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/createaccount.cgi">sign up for a Bugzilla account</a>
and get <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/page.cgi?id=get_permissions.html">"CanConfirm" permissions to modify bugs.</a> 
Once you 've got that, you're ready to go. Please take a moment bdto read these
documents on <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/QA/Triaging_Bugs_for_Firefox">Effective
bug triage for Firefox</a> and best practices for <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/QA/Confirming_unconfirmed_bugs">confirming
unconfirmed bugs</a>.
</p>
